Different types of mycorrhiza (arbuscular, ecto-, ericoid, monotropoid and orchid mycorrhizas), their distribution, evolution, ecology, physiology and its applications in forestry as well as in agriculture will be overviewed. Practical exercises include the microscopy of ecto- and arbuscualr mycorrhizas.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to deas with mycorrhiza - the symbiosis between plant roots and fungi.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successful attendance of the course, students possess basic knowledge of mycorrhizal symbiosis and other fungus-plant root biotic interactions. Students are able to include fungal and mycorrhizal aspects in their botanical, ecological or physiological research.
